Peru:
Fujimori came for medical check-ups once again in the hospital
Former President Alberto Fujimori was hospitalized Tuesday in a public hospital to examine the muscle loss of his legs, his doctor informed.
The 72-year-old Fujimori, 25 years sitting out imprisonment for violation of human rights during his reign (1990-2000), has several diseases, including cancer of the tongue, which operates four times and is under control.
Alejandro Aguinaga, Member of Parliament, and his personal doctor, said on television that Fujimori three days in a Peruvian Hospital of Instituto Nacional de Enfermedades Neoplásicas would investigated to determine the cause of his pain and the loss of muscle in the lower limbs of the body.
Aguinaga commented that he thought Fujimori could be pardoned on humanitarian grounds. Nevertheless he not wanted this, because he considers him innocent.
He was operated on four times on tongue cancer and he has lost 18 kilos weight. To get more diseases such as a severe erosive gastritis, a cyst in the pancreas, kidney stones, high blood pressure and blood circulation problems in his legs, the doctor listed.
Fujimori is since September 2007 in prison Dirección Nacional de operaciones Especiales de la Policía.
In April 2009 he was sentenced prison for the murder of 25 people that while his reign was secretly engaged, to 25 years by the death squad of the Peruvian army.
